Consider a production line that can be modeled as a Markov chain with 5 states, where each state represents a stage in the assembly line. The transition matrix P is given as follows:

P = 
[0.1 0.9 0 0 0;
0.1 0.2 0.7 0 0;
0 0.1 0.3 0.6 0;
0 0 0.1 0.4 0.5;
0 0 0 0.1 0.9]

The production supervisor wants to improve the efficiency of the assembly line. He suggests that by making some changes in the assembly line, the transition probabilities can be adjusted such that the time spent in each state can be minimized.

1. Find the stationary distribution of the Markov chain.
2. If the supervisor suggests that the transition probability from state 2 to state 3 can be increased by 0.1, and the transition probability from state 3 to state 4 can be decreased by 0.1, how would this change affect the stationary distribution?
3. Based on your answer in 2, would the supervisor's suggestion improve the efficiency of the assembly line? Justify your answer.
